nxOOoAutoListen
---------------

OOo has to be launched in listen mode to be driven by external programs
It can be done by hand at each launch by using some command line like

$ /opt/openoffice.org2.1/program/soffice -accept="socket,host=0,port=8100;urp;"

nxOOoAutoListen is an OOo Extension that setup OOo to be in listen mode at every start
Then this has only to be done at setup time and no need to deal with futher command line parameters

- to install

   - for all OOo users 
   $ /opt/openoffice.org2.1/program/unopkg add --shared  nxOOoAutoListen.oxt

   - for the current user
   $ /opt/openoffice.org2.1/program/unopkg add nxOOoAutoListen.oxt

- to uninstall
    replace /add/ by /remove/ in the above lines

For more information on OOo Listen mode, see
http://api.openoffice.org/docs/DevelopersGuide/ProfUNO/ProfUNO.xhtml#1_3_1_1_Starting_OpenOffice.org_in_Listening_Mode